The paper discusses the use of intrinsic motivation to support autonomous learning of complex behaviors, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the use of predictive information as an intrinsic drive, which is a concept that is closely related to reinforcement learning and policy gradient methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
